Ask HN: Do you also hate iOS's rubber-band effect when scrolling?
text:
Every time I scroll all the way up or down, the page bounces back for a second or two, which means I can't quickly press whatever I scrolled for. On Android, (at least v11, the last one I used), I could expect a rock solid scrolling UX, no rubber-band, no eye-candy, to-the-point and predictable.

Given that this "feature" has been in iOS for as long as I can remember, there must be people who like it? Or is it just me who hates it? I also don't like it on macOS, it's as if the page content is "fluid" and there's no stability.

Ask HN: How to handle building a startup for users that need special compliance?
text: Hey all - I have a potential user that's really interested in a product I'm building. However, some of the use cases would involve medical records and the tools they already use advertise HIPPA (and SOC) compliance. I plan to focus on use cases that won't bring HIPPA into scope. But I'm curious to hear how others have approached this. When do you start getting audits and paying for compliance reports?
